            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14011",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=philippe.levan",
                        "name": "philippe.levan",
                        "displayName": "Philippe Le Van",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, I believe the better would be to change the api and say that we can use Zend translate with this kind of code :\n{code}\n$translate = new Zend_Translate(new Zend_Translate_Adapter_Csv('path\/to\/mytranslation.csv', 'de'));\n{code}\nBest regards, Philippe",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=philippe.levan",
                        "name": "philippe.levan",
                        "displayName": "Philippe Le Van",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-05T11:20:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-05T11:20:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14012",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actualy we are supporting all needed adapters and plan to add 3-4 additionaly. See the proposals page.\n\nThere is no known other common adapter. If you are in need of additional propritary adapters you can extend Zend_Translate yourself and implement them this way.\n\nThe intention is that all users can use all known adapters. It would be nonsense if adapters have to be created by the users.\n\nRelated to your second comment... this was discussed by the devteam and it was decided to use the actual way. What you mentioned is not tool friendly. Within the I18N API there is no class which acts like this way. We also have to look to be consistency with existing code\/API.\n\nAnd you can use the Adapter directly without the base translation class. This works already.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-05T14:30:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-05T14:30:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14013",
                    "author": {
